## Summary

Add a `dreaming.language` configuration option so users can make their Dream Diary entries and narrative reflections write in a language other than English.

## Changes

1. **`src/memory-host-sdk/dreaming.ts`** — Add optional `language` field to `MemoryDreamingExecutionConfig` type and propagate it through `resolveExecutionConfig`.
2. **`extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.ts`** — Make `NARRATIVE_SYSTEM_PROMPT` language-aware by reading `dreaming.language` from config at runtime and appending a language instruction to the subagent system prompt.
3. **`docs/concepts/dreaming.md`** — Document the new `language` option.

## Usage

```jsonc
{
  "plugins": {
    "entries": {
      "memory-core": {
        "config": {
          "dreaming": {
            "enabled": true,
            "language": "zh-CN"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Compatibility

- When `language` is unset or empty, behavior is identical to before (English).
- Unknown language codes fall back to English gracefully.
- Only affects the Dream Diary subagent system prompt; MEMORY.md promotion logic is unchanged.
